article.headline: Lehigh 67, Harvard 56
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Kyle Neptune scored a career-high 24 points as Lehigh beat Harvard 67-56 on Saturday. Jose Olivero chipped in 15 points for the Mountain Hawks (4-6) and Bryan White added 11. Matt Stehle led Harvard (5-3) with 13 points and was the only member of the Crimson to break into double figures. Olivero held Harvard's Jim Goffredo -- who came into the game averaging 13.9 points per game -- to eight points on 3-for-15 shooting from the floor. Neptune scored on a coast-to-coast layup with 12:26 left that gave Lehigh a 42-31 lead. Stehle cut Lehigh's lead to four with a three-point play with 6:10 to go, but the Mountain Hawks held the Crimson scoreless the rest of the way. Lehigh shot 14-for-28 from the floor in the first half, building a 33-29 lead going into the break. The Mountain Hawks came into the game shooting 39 percent on the season.
